##More than 1200 confirmed cases, the president's side has infected, why South Korea suddenly become the second largest outbreak of the country

Health insight

Functional introduction, understand the health professional news

South Korea found its first confirmed case on January 20, followed by a month of slow development, until February 18,31 cases were confirmed. Since February 19th it has exploded, with more than 1,200 new cases a week.

Patient number 31, diagnosed on the 18th, is considered a "super spreader. ".
A major feature of the new crown outbreak in South Korea is the presence of concentrated infection within a specific population. The New World Church of Taegu and North Gyeongsang Road, the county hospital is the worst hit area.
The mortality rate of NCP in Korea is about 1% , which is higher than that in non-hubei area of China.
February 23, the South Korean government will be new crown disease alert level raised to the highest level of "serious. ". On February 25, Moon arrived in Taegu to visit first-line anti-epidemic workers and people.

In just one week, South Korea became the largest country outside of China to experience a new outbreak of pneumonia.

As of 4 p.m. on February 26,284 new cases of COVID-19 infection had been confirmed in South Korea, bringing the total to 12 deaths and 1,261 confirmed cases, Yonhap reported.
Photo: Yonhap News Agency; by eight points Jianwen sinicization
Daegu and North Gyeongsang Province are the main affected areas. Daegu, one of South Korea's six "wide-area cities" , and North Gyeongsang Province, one of the eight "Tao" , are first-level administrative country subdivision.

Not only South Korea, Japan, Italy, Iran and other countries have also shown a rapid rise in the number of infected people trend.

Epidemiologists and virologists have long warned of the spread of new coronaviruses outside China. On Feb. 9, Japanese television channel NHK released the world's first documentary on the new coronavirus outbreak, titled: How Much Will The epidemic spread? An urgent report on new pneumonia, the show's host, WHO senior adviser on infectious disease crisis and management, Kuniko Kondo, said at the time that China's controls had led to a sharp decline in overseas patients, but the results were expected to last only until the end of February.

A week ago, on Feb. 18, the number of confirmed cases in South Korea was only 31, meaning the outbreak has been slow to develop in the month since the country's first confirmed case was discovered on Jan. 20. Five days from November 11th to 15th there were no new infections, at one point leading outsiders to believe that the outbreak was under control.
Photo: Yonhap

Why did the situation suddenly change?
The super-communicator and the new World Church of Taegu
The change took place on February 19.

Daegu and the North Gyeongsang Province region experienced a massive spread and collective infection that day, and the numbers have multiplied daily since. The key to the change was patient 31, who was diagnosed on the 18th, the 61-year-old woman is considered a "super-spreader" of the virus. Her Age is 59, according to Yonhap.

The woman, a member of Jesus's Church in Xintiandi, visited a church in Daegu four times before and after her hospital stay, and had 1,160 close contacts. Of the 20 newly diagnosed patients in South Korea on the 19th, 15 were associated with them, most of whom had attended the same church.

As of 9:00 am on the 26th, 501 of the 1,146 confirmed cases were related to the new World Taegu church, accounting for 43.7% , at one point, it was more than 50% . Of the 12 deaths so far, three have been linked to the new world church in Taegu.
The patient, who lives in Daegu city, presented with cold and sore throat for the first time on February 7. He took a bus to the Korea Oriental Hospital in Shoucheng district of Daegu city for treatment. He began to have fever around February 10. During his stay in hospital, he attended church services in southern district of Taegu on 9 and 16, and went out to the hotel for dinner. Until the 18th, testing confirmed that the new coronavirus infection. Given that the Virus latency lasted a maximum of 14 days, the agency investigated the patient's attendance at two services prior to the onset of symptoms, plus two during the hospitalization, for a total of four services.
A Church Service held by Xintiandi Church; screenshot of the promotional video on Xintiandi Church's website

According to public information on the website of the Ministry of Health and Services of Korea, the patient had no overseas travel experience since December 2019, had no contact with a confirmed patient, and could not identify the source and route of infection. Further epidemiological investigations are ongoing.
△ screenshot from the Korean Ministry of Health and services official website of the public information, the original text is Korean, this is the website literal translation version.

Earlier, the 31st patient may have attended the funeral of the brother of the patriarch, which attracted many worshippers. The funeral was held at Qingdaojun Dannan Hospital in North Gyeongsang Province from January 31 to February 2.

Qingdaodanan hospital: 7 deaths due to concentrated infection

A characteristic feature of the new crown outbreak in South Korea is the presence of concentrated infection within a specific population. In addition to the new World Church of Taegu, the other hardest hit area is the Qingdaojun Dannan Hospital in North Gyeongsang Province (referred to as "Qingdaodaonan hospital") , which has a psychiatric ward. Two confirmed cases were first reported on February 19. Statistics as of the morning of February 26, a total of 113 confirmed cases were related to Qingdaodanan hospital, accounting for 9.9% .
Qingdao Danan hospital is located in Qingshang County, North Road, Qingdao, is a general hospital for Geriatric Diseases, the majority of inpatients to the elderly. There were 102 inpatients and 99 confirmed cases in the psychiatric inpatient building of the hospital.

In this epidemic, Qingdaodanan hospital has become a major disaster area, as of 26,12 deaths, 7 cases were classified to the hospital.
Photo: Yonhap News Agency; by eight points Jianwen sinicization

As early as February 19, the Hospital 2 psychiatric ward patients were confirmed infected with the virus, the central epidemic prevention department immediately began to investigate all patients and staff of the hospital. That morning, 109 patients and about 120 hospital staff had their sputum tested. Since the 31st patient had visited Chongdo County in early February before his diagnosis, whether the hospital case was related to him was also the focus of an investigation by Korea's Central Epidemic Prevention Response Department at the time.
On the same day, the hospital suffered the country's first death from pneumonia in a 63-year-old Korean male who had been hospitalized for more than 20 years. The health department tested the patient posthumously for the virus and the result was positive.
The hospital's second death, the second in South Korea, occurred on the afternoon of the 21st. The case, a 54 year old female, was admitted to a psychiatric hospital in Chongdao County, North Gyeongsang Province, where she was admitted to a general ward the day she was diagnosed with the virus and taken by ambulance to Pusan National University. After being transferred to the hospital, he died during treatment at around 5:00 p.m.
Kim woo-ju, professor of infectious medicine at the Korea Jiulao Hospital, said that most of the new crown cases at the South Korean hospital are elderly and frail patients who have been hospitalized for many years and most of them are in critical condition, with the highest mortality rate in the country. This shows that patients may not be receiving proper treatment, it is necessary to take measures as soon as possible to classify the patients as critical and to transfer them to the negative pressure ward of the University Hospital for professional treatment.

In addition to the seven deaths, 25 of the hospital's 106 cases have been transferred to other medical institutions, while the rest have been treated by medical staff sent by the state-run Psychiatric Hospital, Jin Gangli, deputy head of the Central Emergency Management Department, said Tuesday. The government is currently studying a scheme for the transfer of patients with severe illness and has classified patients according to the severity of their illness and will transfer them if necessary, but since most patients are suffering from mental illness at the same time, he said, it's GonNa be hard to get him transferred.

A total of 113 patients, including 103 former patients, nine medical staff and one family member, were admitted to the hospital, 101 of whom were in closed wards, Yonhap reported Thursday.
The death toll from COVID-19 has also directly increased the death rate in South Korea. The death rate from infectious diseases in South Korea is about 1 percent, the country's head of the central epidemic prevention strategy, COVID-19, said on the 26th, the death cases are mainly concentrated in the elderly or patients with underlying diseases. That figure is higher than in non-hubei parts of China.

Zheng Yinjing explained that under normal circumstances the death rate of new coronavirus is not high, but in the elderly or have diabetes, cardiovascular disease mortality rate is higher. The deaths in South Korea were caused by a cluster of infections at the Qingdaonan hospital, where susceptible groups had gathered during the early stages of the outbreak. In order to reduce the death rate of new coronary cases in China, the government will improve the management system, strictly judge the severity of the disease at the initial stage of onset, and centralize the examination and treatment of patients with more serious diseases.
Military, presidential palace infection raises concerns

On February 21, Republic of Korea Armed Forces's forces discovered the first confirmed case. A, who works in the Jeju Volcanic Island and Lava Tubes navy, began to leave for Taegu on the 13th. He returned to Jeju Volcanic Island and Lava Tubes on the afternoon of the 18th by plane and returned to his unit. On the 20th, he returned to the army after being tested for the virus at a hospital screening clinic due to cough and other symptoms. To prevent the spread of the epidemic, South Korea's Ministry of National Defense decided from the 22nd to restrict officers and soldiers from taking leave, going out, sleeping away and visiting, but before retirement, bereavement leave and other special cases.

To 23 noon, the South Korean army and air force have found confirmed cases, army 4, Navy 1, Air Force 1, a total of 6 people, are outside the camp infection. On the 24th, the figure rose to 11.

South Korea's Defense Ministry believes that once the epidemic spread within the force will lead to the situation out of control, so the military to expand the scope of quarantine and other further escalation of control measures. As of the 23rd, more than 7,700 South Korean troops were quarantined, and the military has strengthened control measures in accordance with the guidelines of the Ministry of National Defense. The Army, Navy, Air Force and Marine Corps have been carrying out a comprehensive survey since February 10 of officers and soldiers travelling on leave or on leave to the Taegu and Gyeongbuk regions.

The military infection not only occurred in the South Korean army, even affected the U. S. troops in South Korea.

An American soldier in the South Korean List of United States Army installations in South Korea of North Gyeongsang Province was found to have COVID-19 infection Tuesday. The soldier is now living in isolation in his dormitory outside the base. He has been living in Camp Carroll, South Korea since the 21st and visited Camp Walker in Daegu on the 24th.

In view of the sudden increase in confirmed cases in the city of Daegu and North Gyeongsang Province, the U. S. military in South Korea raised its alert level from Low to Moderate on the 19th, and then to High on the 25th. Under the new alert level, the US military will restrict the flow of troops in and out of the country, with restrictions on meetings, gatherings and temporary deployments, except for essential tasks. The US military has also imposed a total ban on officers and soldiers taking leave or going out for personal reasons. It has advised the bases to avoid the movement of personnel, but there has been no move to withdraw their families back to the mainland.

As with military infections, an infection inside Blue House would be a sensitive matter of concern. A similar incident did occur around South Korea's president, Moon jae-in.

Moon, who arrived in Taegu on Feb. 25 to greet first-line disease fighters and people and to host a meeting on the COVID-19 response to the epidemic, said a turning point in containing the virus must be seen this week.

At the meeting, Moon and his team prayed for a moment of silence for the sick and the dead. What he did not know at the time was that the secretary of the deputy mayor of the city of Daegu, who was attending the meeting, would be the confirmed case because the secretary's test results had not yet been released.

After the news, the Blue House recommended that the relevant people and media reporters who were present at the meeting to implement a seven-day home quarantine. If you develop fever or respiratory disease symptoms during isolation, you should call the department's emergency hotline (1339) or the district health station and follow the instructions to the screening clinic.

On the whole, the Korean government is timely in its prevention and control, but still faces many challenges from citizens and believers, such as the downtown assembly.

The South Korean government raised the alert level for the new outbreak from "concern" to "attention" after finding the first confirmed case on January 20, and then again to "alert" , up to the highest level "serious" on February 23.

According to Yonhap News Agency, South Korea's infectious disease alert level from low to high is divided into four stages, namely attention, attention, vigilance, serious. This is the Korean government in 2009 H1N1 influenza a after 11 years to issue the highest level of infectious disease alert again. After issuing a "serious" warning, the government can take the highest-level response measures, including ordering the closure of schools at all levels, banning collective activities.

After being transferred to the hospital, he died during treatment at around 5:00 p.m.

Kim woo-ju, professor of infectious medicine at the Korea Jiulao Hospital, said that most of the new crown cases at the South Korean hospital are elderly and frail patients who have been hospitalized for many years and most of them are in critical condition, with the highest mortality rate in the country. This shows that patients may not be receiving proper treatment, it is necessary to take measures as soon as possible to classify the patients as critical and to transfer them to the negative pressure ward of the University Hospital for professional treatment.

In addition to the seven deaths, 25 of the hospital's 106 cases have been transferred to other medical institutions, while the rest have been treated by medical staff sent by the state-run Psychiatric Hospital, Jin Gangli, deputy head of the Central Emergency Management Department, said Tuesday. The government is currently studying a scheme for the transfer of patients with severe illness and has classified patients according to the severity of their illness and will transfer them if necessary, but since most patients are suffering from mental illness at the same time, he said, it's GonNa be hard to get him transferred.

A total of 113 patients, including 103 former patients, nine medical staff and one family member, were admitted to the hospital, 101 of whom were in closed wards, Yonhap reported Thursday.

The death toll from COVID-19 has also directly increased the death rate in South Korea. The death rate from infectious diseases in South Korea is about 1 percent, the country's head of the central epidemic prevention strategy, COVID-19, said on the 26th, the death cases are mainly concentrated in the elderly or patients with underlying diseases. That figure is higher than in non-hubei parts of China.

Zheng Yinjing explained that under normal circumstances the death rate of new coronavirus is not high, but in the elderly or have diabetes, cardiovascular disease mortality rate is higher. The deaths in South Korea were caused by a cluster of infections at the Qingdaonan hospital, where susceptible groups had gathered during the early stages of the outbreak. In order to reduce the death rate of new coronary cases in China, the government will improve the management system, strictly judge the severity of the disease at the initial stage of onset, and centralize the examination and treatment of patients with more serious diseases.

###Military, presidential palace infection raises concerns

Military, presidential palace infection raises concerns

On February 21, Republic of Korea Armed Forces's forces discovered the first confirmed case. A, who works in the Jeju Volcanic Island and Lava Tubes navy, began to leave for Taegu on the 13th. He returned to Jeju Volcanic Island and Lava Tubes on the afternoon of the 18th by plane and returned to his unit. On the 20th, he returned to the army after being tested for the virus at a hospital screening clinic due to cough and other symptoms. To prevent the spread of the epidemic, South Korea's Ministry of National Defense decided from the 22nd to restrict officers and soldiers from taking leave, going out, sleeping away and visiting, but before retirement, bereavement leave and other special cases.

To 23 noon, the South Korean army and air force have found confirmed cases, army 4, Navy 1, Air Force 1, a total of 6 people, are outside the camp infection. On the 24th, the figure rose to 11.

South Korea's Defense Ministry believes that once the epidemic spread within the force will lead to the situation out of control, so the military to expand the scope of quarantine and other further escalation of control measures. As of the 23rd, more than 7,700 South Korean troops were quarantined, and the military has strengthened control measures in accordance with the guidelines of the Ministry of National Defense. The Army, Navy, Air Force and Marine Corps have been carrying out a comprehensive survey since February 10 of officers and soldiers travelling on leave or on leave to the Taegu and Gyeongbuk regions.

The military infection not only occurred in the South Korean army, even affected the U. S. troops in South Korea.

An American soldier in the South Korean List of United States Army installations in South Korea of North Gyeongsang Province was found to have COVID-19 infection Tuesday. The soldier is now living in isolation in his dormitory outside the base. He has been living in Camp Carroll, South Korea since the 21st and visited Camp Walker in Daegu on the 24th.

In view of the sudden increase in confirmed cases in the city of Daegu and North Gyeongsang Province, the U. S. military in South Korea raised its alert level from Low to Moderate on the 19th, and then to High on the 25th. Under the new alert level, the US military will restrict the flow of troops in and out of the country, with restrictions on meetings, gatherings and temporary deployments, except for essential tasks. The US military has also imposed a total ban on officers and soldiers taking leave or going out for personal reasons. It has advised the bases to avoid the movement of personnel, but there has been no move to withdraw their families back to the mainland.

As with military infections, an infection inside Blue House would be a sensitive matter of concern. A similar incident did occur around South Korea's president, Moon jae-in.

Moon, who arrived in Taegu on Feb. 25 to greet first-line disease fighters and people and to host a meeting on the COVID-19 response to the epidemic, said a turning point in containing the virus must be seen this week.

At the meeting, Moon and his team prayed for a moment of silence for the sick and the dead. What he did not know at the time was that the secretary of the deputy mayor of the city of Daegu, who was attending the meeting, would be the confirmed case because the secretary's test results had not yet been released.

After the news, the Blue House recommended that the relevant people and media reporters who were present at the meeting to implement a seven-day home quarantine. If you develop fever or respiratory disease symptoms during isolation, you should call the department's emergency hotline (1339) or the district health station and follow the instructions to the screening clinic.

On the whole, the Korean government is timely in its prevention and control, but still faces many challenges from citizens and believers, such as the downtown assembly.

The South Korean government raised the alert level for the new outbreak from "concern" to "attention" after finding the first confirmed case on January 20, and then again to "alert" , up to the highest level "serious" on February 23.

According to Yonhap News Agency, South Korea's infectious disease alert level from low to high is divided into four stages, namely attention, attention, vigilance, serious. This is the Korean government in 2009 H1N1 influenza a after 11 years to issue the highest level of infectious disease alert again. After issuing a "serious" warning, the government can take the highest-level response measures, including ordering the closure of schools at all levels, banning collective activities.
